org.xlbean

Class XlBeanImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object>
        • org.xlbean.XlBeanImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object>, XlBean
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SimpleXlBeanFactory.SimpleXlBean

    public class XlBeanImpl
extends java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object>
implements XlBean
    Implementation of XlBean which inherits HashMap.

    Override put(String, Object) to validate a object given to the method before actually put it to this map, in order to prevent unexpected behavior which will be caused by various types of values in this map which are not supported by this library by default. However, as long as you are sure about the types of the values, the validation can be omitted or changed to other logic by overriding canPut(Object).

      • beanOf

        public <T> T beanOf(java.lang.String sourceKey,
                    java.lang.Class<T> destinationClass)
        Description copied from interface: XlBean
        Returns the object of destinationClass filled with the contents mapped from a Map retrieved by sourceKey.

        If an object retrieved by sourceKey is null or not Map instance, then it returns blank instance of destinationClass.

        Mapping from Map of sourceKey to instance of destinationClass is key to property mapping. Refer to BeanConverter for further detail.

        Specified by:
        beanOf in interface XlBean
        Returns:
